Description:
Our Company
Founded in 1977, CARMA is 100% Canadian owned and operated, with its head office and manufacturing facility located in Lindsay, Ontario. We were the first Measurement Canada approved supplier of electronic submetering systems and continue to be the market leader, with over 250,000 meters installed. Operating across Canada with offices in Toronto, Ottawa, Edmonton, Calgary and Vancouver. CARMA ensures first-rate customer care, regulatory compliance, quality control, financial tracking and accountability.
We are looking to add a full time
Accounting Specialist
to our Lindsay team.
Accounting Specialist Responsibilities
Perform periodic accounting activities including reconciliations of accounts, coordination and completion of annual audits, and reviewing financial reports/support as necessary;
Participate in all aspects of Accounts Receivable and/or Accounts Payable; the collection aspects of Accounts Receivable, administer daily collection calls to confirm accurate billing, invoice receipt and payment status, escalate aged accounts to collection action and apply credit holds; prepare and enter all accounts payable documents, ensure proper coding, profit centre allocation, accounting period;
Analyze and report on financial status including income statement variances, budget variances and period over period, communicating financial results to management;
Summarizes current financial status by collecting information; preparing Financial Statements, and other reports; participate in preparation for the annual audit;
Review the company’s accounting information to identify and resolve inaccuracies; substantiate financial transactions by auditing documents.
Assist in the formulation of internal controls and policies to comply with legislation and established best practices; improve systems and procedures and initiate corrective actions;
Assist in the preparation of financial statements in compliance with official guidelines and requirements; manage journal entries, invoices etc. and reconcile accounts for periodic closing;
Help in development of reports for management or regulatory bodies; assist in the preparation of budgets or forecasts;
Assist with the management of short & long-term contracts/projects; monitor progress, prepare documentation, verify schedules and calculations; generate reports & maintain databases;
Setup, calculate and maintain schedules such as deprecation, prepaid and deposits; reconcile schedules to general ledger and compile supporting documentation;
Maintain files and documentation thoroughly and accurately, in accordance with company policy and accepted accounting practices.
Experience/Knowledge/Ability
5+ years accounting experience;
Numerical Competence; ability to solve complex problems, manage and analyze data;
Excellent communication and administrative skills; accuracy and attention to detail;
Exceptional organization and time management skills; ability to multitask and manage demanding workload with tight deadlines;
Teamwork, willingness to work collaboratively and assist department in meeting deadlines;
Professionalism, integrity and Compliance;
Experience preparing Financial Statements;
Solid knowledge of GAAP (Generally Accepted Accounting Principles) and regulations;
Excellent knowledge of accounting and financial processes (budgeting, financial closure, reporting etc.);
Understanding of data analysis and forecasting.
Qualifications
Post-Secondary School Graduate in Business and/or Accounting Diploma, preferred;
CPA designation is an asset;
Sage 300 ERP and Sage Business Intelligence experience;
Computer proficiency with Microsoft applications.
Working Conditions
Office environment using computer;
Demanding workload & tight deadlines;
Occasionally required to work evenings and/or weekends to meet period end reporting deadlines.
We thank you for your interest; however, only successful applicants will be contacted.
